New Records: RJ Barrett had his first triple-double with 25 points, 15 assists, and 10 rebounds, the first Raptors player ever with all that in the same game.
Key Match Events: Jayson Tatum hit a 3-pointer at the buzzer in overtime to give the Celtics a 126-123 victory.
Jakob Poeltl scored a career-high 35 points and had 12 rebounds.
Neemias Queta blocked RJ Barrett's driving layup attempt, giving the ball back to the Celtics with 20.2 seconds remaining.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Raptors outscored the Celtics 76-42 in the paint.
Boston Celtics improved to 11-3 and avoided losing for the third time at TD Garden this season.
